1. Login to Web Console

2. Copy Oozie example
	 /usr/hdp/current/oozie-client/doc/oozie-examples.tar.gz (to your home directory in web console)

3. Extract files from tar
	 tar -zxvf oozie-examples.tar.gz

4. Edit examples/apps/map-reduce/job.properties and set:
	 nameNode = hdfs://ip-172-31-38-146.ec2.internal:8020
	 jobTracker = ip-172-31-38-146.ec2.internal:8050
	 queueName = default
	 examplesRoot = examples
	 
5. Copy the examples directory to HDFS
	hadoop fs -copyFromLocal examples
	
6. Run the job
	oozie job -oozie http://ip-172-31-13-154.ec2.internal:11000/oozie -config examples/app/map-reduce/job.properties -run
	
7. Check the job status
	oozie job-oozie http://ip-172-31-13-154.ec2.internal:11000/oozie -info job_id
